{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01F3CfmP9itAKyevLkKWxJfL","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package quarkus.tutorial.roster.entity;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.persistence.*;\n     4→import java.io.Serializable;\n     5→import java.util.ArrayList;\n     6→import java.util.Collection;\n     7→\n     8→@Entity\n     9→public class Team implements Serializable {\n    10→    private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    11→\n    12→    @Id\n    13→    private String id;\n    14→    private String name;\n    15→    private String city;\n    16→    @ManyToMany\n    17→    private Collection<Player> players = new ArrayList<>();\n    18→    @ManyToOne\n    19→    private League league;\n    20→\n    21→    public Team() {\n    22→    }\n    23→\n    24→    public Team(String id, String name, String city) {\n    25→        this.id = id;\n    26→        this.name = name;\n    27→        this.city = city;\n    28→    }\n    29→\n    30→    public String getId() {\n    31→        return id;\n    32→    }\n    33→\n    34→    public void setId(String id) {\n    35→        this.id = id;\n    36→    }\n    37→\n    38→    public String getName() {\n    39→        return name;\n    40→    }\n    41→\n    42→    public void setName(String name) {\n    43→        this.name = name;\n    44→    }\n    45→\n    46→    public String getCity() {\n    47→        return city;\n    48→    }\n    49→\n    50→    public void setCity(String city) {\n    51→        this.city = city;\n    52→    }\n    53→\n    54→    public Collection<Player> getPlayers() {\n    55→        return players;\n    56→    }\n    57→\n    58→    public void setPlayers(Collection<Player> players) {\n    59→        this.players = players;\n    60→    }\n    61→\n    62→    public League getLeague() {\n    63→        return league;\n    64→    }\n    65→\n    66→    public void setLeague(League league) {\n    67→        this.league = league;\n    68→    }\n    69→\n    70→    public void addPlayer(Player player) {\n    71→        this.players.add(player);\n    72→    }\n    73→\n    74→    public void dropPlayer(Player player) {\n    75→        this.players.remove(player);\n    76→    }\n    77→}\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Ezyu4jNmaqUNRX2P4zv2Wu","session_id":"d9729fc2-69e7-40e2-ad86-5630b00c4ba7","uuid":"8ef755bb-2426-4a01-b212-4e9a26020e0f"}
