{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01WuwmBtzA7xyGyDBx9tgFqp","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The logs don't show enough detail. Let me look at the `createLeague` method more closely. The issue is that when the `createLeague` method catches exceptions and re-throws as `WebApplicationException(ex, BAD_REQUEST)`, the original exception gets wrapped. With EclipseLink (Open Liberty's JPA provider), the issue is likely that:\n\n1. The `createLeague` method tries to persist, gets an exception, and wraps it as a 400 BAD_REQUEST\n2. The root cause is probably a transaction issue - the `@Transactional` annotation requires a JTA transaction manager\n\nLet me check if the issue is with the `@Transactional` interceptor not being enabled, or with the JPA metamodel, or with JSON deserialization. Let me check:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1595,"cache_read_input_tokens":106657,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1595,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":305},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d9729fc2-69e7-40e2-ad86-5630b00c4ba7","uuid":"56c5e6ac-4da8-479c-871d-f3d9d28a1d1f"}
