{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_0114BjB3Z1z25G2KoXgMCS19","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The error isn't very informative. The issue is that the `createLeague` method catches all exceptions and wraps them as BAD_REQUEST. Looking at the code flow:\n\n```java\npublic void createLeague(LeagueDetails leagueDetails) {\n    try {\n        String sport = leagueDetails.getSport().toLowerCase();\n        ...\n        SummerLeague league = new SummerLeague(leagueDetails.getId(), ...);\n        em.persist(league);\n        em.flush();\n    } catch (Exception ex) {\n        throw new WebApplicationException(ex, Response.Status.BAD_REQUEST);\n    }\n}\n```\n\nThe problem is likely that `leagueDetails` is `null` - meaning JSON deserialization failed. Open Liberty uses JSON-B (not Jackson) by default for JSON serialization. `LeagueDetails` doesn't have setters - only getter methods and a constructor. JSON-B needs either public fields or setters.\n\nLet me check - `LeagueDetails` has a no-arg constructor and `getId()`, `getName()`, `getSport()` getters but NO setters. JSON-B needs setters (or public fields) to deserialize. The same applies to `TeamDetails` and `PlayerDetails`.\n\nLet me add setters to the detail classes:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":452,"cache_read_input_tokens":108869,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":452,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":421},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d9729fc2-69e7-40e2-ad86-5630b00c4ba7","uuid":"7b40ef6f-95ab-460a-bf3f-aa51648010bd"}
